# SkillWise Deployment Architecture Prepared

I've successfully updated your codebase to support a **zero-cost, unified cloud deployment** using Hugging Face Spaces!

Here's a breakdown of the specific architectural changes and configurations we executed.

## 1. Internal Networking Simplified
Instead of splitting your resources across Render and Hugging Face, the entire brain of SkillWise now lives in one container.

> [!NOTE]
> **Port Assignments**
> *   `Port 7860`: Bound to the Express server (this is the only port Hugging Face exposes to the internet).
> *   `Port 5000`: Bound to FastAPI (Proctoring/CNN) running locally.
> *   `Port 8000`: Bound to ML-Service (Adaptive Questioning) running locally.
> 
> The Express server acts as a unified gateway, automatically reverse-proxying requests made to `/api/proctoring` inward to Port 5000.

## 2. Containerization Built
I created the monorepo deployment formula that Hugging Face Spaces requires:

*   [**Dockerfile**](file:///c:/Users/acer/Desktop/DL%20Project/Dockerfile): Automates the installation of Node.js 18 alongside Python 3.10. It processes the requirements for all three subdirectories.
*   [**start.sh**](file:///c:/Users/acer/Desktop/DL%20Project/start.sh): Ensures a synchronized startup sequence, launching both Python APIs in the background before attaching the Express gateway to the foreground.

## 3. Environment Variables Integrated
The frontend must understand where it is hosted compared to where the backend lives.

*   Updated `api.js` and `socket.js` to look for `VITE_API_URL` instead of relying on the local Vite proxy.
*   Updated `environment.js` and `proctoringAdapter.js` in the Express server to use `PROCTOR_URL` and `ML_SERVICE_URL`.

